170 g Fusilli
2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
1 unit(s) Cream Cheese
227 g Mushrooms
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
56 g Green Peas
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
½ tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ cup Milk*

Add fusilli to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 9-11 min.
Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water, then drain and return fusilli to the same pot, off heat.

Thinly slice mushrooms.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties and soy sauce. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.** Season with salt and pepper.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer the Beyond Meat® to a bowl.

Add mushrooms, peas, onions and garlic to the same pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, 3-4 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium.
Return Beyond Meat® to the pan. Stir to combine.
Sprinkle over Cream Sauce Spice Blend. Cook, stirring often, until veggies and Beyond Meat® are coated, 1 min.

Add cream cheese, broth concentrate, garlic, 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) milk and reserved pasta water. Cook, stirring often, until slightly thickened, 2-3 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Add Beyond Meat® mixture to the pot with noodles. Stir to combine.
Divide creamy Beyond Meat® fusili between bowls.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook and plate it the same way as the beef, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**